POPULAR skitmakers and actors led by Mr Macaroni, Broda Shaggi, and MC Lively have featured in a Tunice Entertainment project entitled ‘Survivor.’ The trio were featured in the flick which has Kayode Peters as the director.   Nollywood needs more funding, says Wale Muraina     Real Housewives Of Lagos: Laura vindicated, Chioma parts way…     ‘I get my story from real life experiences’   According to a statement from Tunice Entertainment, ‘Survivor’ is directed by John Esedafe and also features I Go Save, Chinonso Arubayi, Chris Iheuwa, and Tony Akposheri among others. The film was premiered at Ebony Life Place on Sunday, June 26, 2022, with several industry practitioners and entertainers in attendance. It started showing in cinemas on Friday, July 1, 2022. ‘Survivors’ follows the story of Gideon (Shaggi) and Zacchaeus (Macaroni), two low-income earning mechanics on a quest to become rich. Events take a drastic turn when they meet David (MC Lively), who introduces them to his boss thus involving them in the business of kidnapping.